WEBVTT

00:00:00.550 --> 00:00:01.550
Huh?

00:00:01.620 --> 00:00:02.636
You want to take time off?

00:00:02.660 --> 00:00:03.660
Yes.

00:00:03.750 --> 00:00:06.550
If we don't take a break now,
things are just going to get crazy again.

00:00:06.830 --> 00:00:08.886
So I figured if we're going to go
anywhere together, it has to be now.

00:00:08.910 --> 00:00:09.910
That's true.

00:00:09.990 --> 00:00:11.599
Once the Christmas collection launches,

00:00:11.600 --> 00:00:13.310
taking a long vacation will be impossible.

00:00:15.430 --> 00:00:17.550
And you'll need to start
getting ready for Paris soon.

00:00:20.450 --> 00:00:23.220
Let's coordinate our days off, then.

00:00:24.020 --> 00:00:25.020
Okay.

00:00:25.530 --> 00:00:27.050
Anywhere in particular you want to go?

00:00:28.820 --> 00:00:29.820
Hmm...

00:00:30.640 --> 00:00:31.890
Maybe a hot spring resort?

00:00:33.780 --> 00:00:34.940
Hold on, let me look some up.

00:00:35.950 --> 00:00:37.910
Hot springs, hot springs...

00:00:38.110 --> 00:00:39.960
I was thinking an overnight trip.

00:00:40.430 --> 00:00:42.250
Hmm... where should we go?

00:00:42.450 --> 00:00:43.670
Maybe Beppu?

00:00:44.440 --> 00:00:45.230
Atami?

00:00:45.231 --> 00:00:46.410
Or Hakone?

00:00:47.060 --> 00:00:48.060
Whoa...

00:00:48.250 --> 00:00:49.550
The mountains!

00:00:53.330 --> 00:00:54.830
Yahoo!

00:00:56.230 --> 00:00:57.230
Natsume-san,

00:00:57.500 --> 00:00:58.510
you're way too excited.

00:01:00.310 --> 00:01:02.100
It's been so long since I've traveled.

00:01:02.630 --> 00:01:05.010
I actually haven't seen much of Japan.

00:01:05.300 --> 00:01:07.330
I'm always being sent abroad for work.

00:01:07.670 --> 00:01:08.740
I'm the exact opposite.

00:01:09.100 --> 00:01:11.820
I travel domestically a lot,
but I've barely been out of the country.

00:01:12.970 --> 00:01:15.249
Then let's go abroad next time.

00:01:15.250 --> 00:01:16.250
Oh...

00:01:25.410 --> 00:01:27.350
Should we grab a bite and take a break?

00:01:27.430 --> 00:01:28.430
Sure.

00:01:28.620 --> 00:01:30.580
Let's find some local specialties to eat!

00:01:32.450 --> 00:01:33.740
Up until now,

00:01:34.800 --> 00:01:37.630
I've only ever been on the receiving end
of Touma's affection.

00:01:38.890 --> 00:01:40.330
I'll take over the
driving for a bit.

00:01:41.340 --> 00:01:42.570
I've never really been the one

00:01:43.560 --> 00:01:45.920
to just say "I love you" out of the blue.

00:01:47.360 --> 00:01:48.360
So,

00:01:49.650 --> 00:01:51.010
on this trip,

00:01:53.550 --> 00:01:54.750
I'm definitely going to...

00:01:55.390 --> 00:01:56.930
tell him I love him myself.

00:01:57.750 --> 00:01:59.840
Thanks for waiting.
Here's your Ramen Houtou.

00:01:59.860 --> 00:02:01.630
And the Shingen Houtou.

00:02:01.640 --> 00:02:02.640
Enjoy your meal.

00:02:02.740 --> 00:02:04.260
We also have the simmered horse offal,

00:02:05.610 --> 00:02:07.300
and the simmered chicken giblets.

00:02:07.680 --> 00:02:10.410
Wow, this looks amazing.

00:02:11.350 --> 00:02:12.350
Let's eat!

00:02:12.550 --> 00:02:13.550
Let's eat!

00:02:15.000 --> 00:02:16.230
Man...

00:02:32.570 --> 00:02:33.850
This is so good!

00:02:34.170 --> 00:02:35.240
You've gotta try some.

00:02:35.490 --> 00:02:36.490
Okay.

00:02:47.640 --> 00:02:48.880
This one's delicious too.

00:02:54.660 --> 00:02:56.000
Everything is so tasty.

00:02:59.600 --> 00:03:02.100
Hey, try a bite of mine.

00:03:02.510 --> 00:03:03.510
Sure.

00:03:10.650 --> 00:03:12.330
It really is good.

00:03:13.350 --> 00:03:14.750
- Let me try yours too.
- Here.

00:03:17.980 --> 00:03:18.980
Go ahead.

00:03:26.030 --> 00:03:28.780
Wow, the flavor is totally different.

00:03:30.340 --> 00:03:31.420
You look so happy.

00:03:32.300 --> 00:03:33.300
Huh?

00:03:55.790 --> 00:03:56.790
Hey, Touma.

00:04:01.310 --> 00:04:01.950
It's getting chilly.

00:04:01.951 --> 00:04:03.730
Welcome! A table for three?

00:04:04.030 --> 00:04:05.030
Right this way.

00:04:05.410 --> 00:04:06.449
We're finally here. What should we get?

00:04:06.450 --> 00:04:08.189
I heard the Ramen Houtou
is famous here.

00:04:08.190 --> 00:04:09.450
That sounds good.

00:04:11.360 --> 00:04:12.460
Not right now.

00:04:14.110 --> 00:04:15.110
It's nothing.

00:04:17.270 --> 00:04:18.270
Yeah.

00:04:20.850 --> 00:04:22.450
Delicious.

00:05:18.800 --> 00:05:22.800
"Cosmetic Playlover Season 2"
(Episode 7)

00:05:24.510 --> 00:05:25.550
Natsume-san,

00:05:25.870 --> 00:05:26.950
what are you eating?

00:05:28.180 --> 00:05:29.380
An onsen manju.

00:05:29.740 --> 00:05:30.740
What's the filling?

00:05:31.370 --> 00:05:32.370
Sweet red bean paste.

00:05:32.690 --> 00:05:34.380
It's really good. Want one?

00:05:34.870 --> 00:05:36.150
Thanks.

00:05:51.350 --> 00:05:52.790
- Good, right?
- Yeah, it is.

00:06:09.410 --> 00:06:10.490
We should walk on the side.

00:06:12.050 --> 00:06:13.910
The middle is the path for the gods.

00:06:15.310 --> 00:06:18.230
- First, wash your hands.
- Okay.

00:06:22.290 --> 00:06:23.290
Then rinse your mouth.

00:06:29.640 --> 00:06:32.610
And then, wash them one more time.

00:06:38.400 --> 00:06:39.400
Here.

00:06:39.600 --> 00:06:40.700
Thank you.

00:07:18.560 --> 00:07:20.450
You were praying for a long time.

00:07:21.310 --> 00:07:22.310
I guess I was.

00:07:23.060 --> 00:07:24.060
Let's go get fortunes!

00:07:26.100 --> 00:07:27.100
Okay.

00:07:28.130 --> 00:07:30.540
I'll go with that one.

00:07:31.830 --> 00:07:32.830
This one.

00:07:36.660 --> 00:07:37.900
Okay, let's open them together.

00:07:39.240 --> 00:07:40.240
Ready...

00:07:45.590 --> 00:07:46.690
Oh! Great Blessing!

00:07:47.150 --> 00:07:48.880
I got Middle Blessing.

00:07:51.750 --> 00:07:52.750
Let's see...

00:07:57.150 --> 00:07:58.280
What does yours say?

00:07:58.340 --> 00:07:59.830
It says things will work out for us.

00:08:02.040 --> 00:08:03.140
What about yours?

00:08:05.270 --> 00:08:07.250
Sincerity leads to success.

00:08:07.430 --> 00:08:08.430
Nice.

00:08:10.190 --> 00:08:11.650
Let's tie them up here.

00:08:32.390 --> 00:08:33.990
That road had so many curves.

00:08:34.230 --> 00:08:36.710
But I haven't driven in a while,
so it was actually pretty fun.

00:08:38.460 --> 00:08:39.320
What's wrong?

00:08:39.321 --> 00:08:40.340
Are you carsick?

00:08:41.390 --> 00:08:42.390
Yeah...

00:08:42.610 --> 00:08:43.880
I'll be fine once I rest a bit.

00:08:49.360 --> 00:08:51.700
This room is incredible!

00:08:53.280 --> 00:08:54.480
It's huge!

00:08:55.340 --> 00:08:59.750
So big!

00:09:02.320 --> 00:09:03.640
And it has its own open-air bath!

00:09:04.050 --> 00:09:05.900
You're like a little kid.

00:09:12.340 --> 00:09:14.990
Is your motion sickness okay?

00:09:15.510 --> 00:09:16.510
Yeah.

00:09:16.650 --> 00:09:17.650
I'm fine.

00:09:18.450 --> 00:09:19.450
Are you sure?

00:09:20.940 --> 00:09:22.010
Positive.

00:09:22.460 --> 00:09:23.460
Good.

00:09:25.940 --> 00:09:28.430
We still have some time before dinner.

00:09:30.030 --> 00:09:31.030
Okay.

00:09:31.180 --> 00:09:32.730
Let's go to the public bath!

00:09:33.770 --> 00:09:34.770
Not right now.

00:09:34.770 --> 00:09:35.770
Huh?

00:09:35.890 --> 00:09:38.580
If you want a soak,
use the one in the room.

00:09:38.610 --> 00:09:39.040
What?

00:09:39.040 --> 00:09:40.040
Why?

00:09:40.090 --> 00:09:41.890
I mean, I'll definitely
use the room one too,

00:09:42.010 --> 00:09:43.860
but we have to hit the big one first!

00:09:46.380 --> 00:09:47.890
The public bath is a no-go.

00:09:48.460 --> 00:09:49.950
I checked at the front desk earlier.

00:09:49.980 --> 00:09:51.730
There's a large tour group using it now.

00:09:52.050 --> 00:09:52.730
Oh.

00:09:52.730 --> 00:09:53.330
If you want to go,

00:09:53.331 --> 00:09:55.260
we should wait until they're at dinner.

00:09:55.330 --> 00:09:57.610
Between 6:00 and 7:30 should be fine.

00:09:58.050 --> 00:09:59.050
You...

00:09:59.110 --> 00:10:00.670
actually went and checked the times?

00:10:03.110 --> 00:10:04.280
Of course I did.

00:10:07.220 --> 00:10:09.700
Fine, I get it. Don't look at me like that.

00:10:10.720 --> 00:10:11.880
Alright, alright.

00:10:17.300 --> 00:10:18.980
That gift shop we saw was pretty nice.

00:10:19.250 --> 00:10:21.010
- Let's go check it out later.
- Sounds good.

00:10:22.170 --> 00:10:24.820
Man, hot spring inns are the best.

00:10:25.290 --> 00:10:27.300
I'm so glad we splurged on this place.

00:10:28.000 --> 00:10:29.000
Me too.

00:10:31.310 --> 00:10:32.519
Ah, this is the life.

00:10:32.520 --> 00:10:34.119
Yeah, it feels great.

00:10:34.120 --> 00:10:35.490
What should we do tomorrow?

00:10:35.580 --> 00:10:37.490
Hmm, I wonder...

00:10:40.480 --> 00:10:41.680
Is something wrong?

00:10:42.610 --> 00:10:43.610
No.

00:10:43.840 --> 00:10:46.000
I was just thinking how nice this is.

00:10:50.380 --> 00:10:51.380
It really is.

00:10:54.820 --> 00:10:56.380
The bath should be empty by now, right?

00:10:57.420 --> 00:10:59.300
- Let's go, Touma.
- Okay.

00:11:01.470 --> 00:11:02.470
Oh.

00:11:02.750 --> 00:11:04.360
I forgot I still have my earrings on.

00:11:05.513 --> 00:11:07.426
I should probably take
them off before I get in.

00:11:07.450 --> 00:11:09.150
I think it's fine.

00:11:09.480 --> 00:11:10.879
As long as you aren't swimming laps.

00:11:10.880 --> 00:11:12.280
Who swims in a hot spring?

00:11:18.610 --> 00:11:19.610
Ah...

00:11:20.850 --> 00:11:22.370
This feels so good.

00:11:24.360 --> 00:11:25.660
Yeah.

00:11:28.450 --> 00:11:29.450
Hey.

00:11:29.710 --> 00:11:32.220
They have a rock bath, a jacuzzi,
and a sauna over there!

00:11:34.700 --> 00:11:37.070
Stop running around naked.

00:11:37.110 --> 00:11:38.110
Why?

00:11:38.630 --> 00:11:40.400
We're here, so I want to try them all!

00:11:52.090 --> 00:11:53.190
I'm beat...

00:11:56.900 --> 00:11:58.920
That was a great soak.

00:11:59.500 --> 00:12:00.500
Here.

00:12:01.010 --> 00:12:02.010
Thanks.

00:12:17.320 --> 00:12:18.320
So good!

00:12:23.460 --> 00:12:24.560
Are you okay?

00:12:25.140 --> 00:12:26.140
Did you get lightheaded?

00:12:28.480 --> 00:12:29.480
A little.

00:12:30.220 --> 00:12:32.880
Carsick, bath-drunk...
I didn't know you had this side to you.

00:12:33.360 --> 00:12:36.150
It's just that you have too much energy.

00:12:53.740 --> 00:12:54.740
Touma...

00:12:59.490 --> 00:13:00.050
About that...

00:13:00.051 --> 00:13:01.450
Let's have a pillow fight!

00:13:01.690 --> 00:13:04.170
- Yeah!
- Hey! Get back here!

00:13:09.110 --> 00:13:10.110
What?

00:13:10.420 --> 00:13:11.420
Nothing.

00:13:14.040 --> 00:13:15.500
Oh, it's almost time for dinner.

00:13:16.030 --> 00:13:17.030
Should we head back?

00:13:17.430 --> 00:13:19.040
Yeah, let's go.

00:13:19.580 --> 00:13:20.860
Let's head back.

00:13:21.630 --> 00:13:22.630
Wait...

00:13:22.900 --> 00:13:23.900
Ah.

00:13:25.770 --> 00:13:27.270
I'm so full...

00:13:27.530 --> 00:13:29.700
I don't want to move a muscle.

00:13:34.460 --> 00:13:37.360
Don't just sit there. Come veg out with me.

00:13:39.120 --> 00:13:40.120
Okay.

00:13:44.400 --> 00:13:45.400
Wait, here?

00:13:46.140 --> 00:13:47.490
I'm sleeping here too.

00:13:47.990 --> 00:13:48.990
Okay.

00:13:50.630 --> 00:13:51.980
You're hopeless.

00:13:52.840 --> 00:13:53.840
Yeah.

00:14:08.750 --> 00:14:11.830
You've been really
exhausted lately, haven't you?

00:14:16.320 --> 00:14:18.030
Between the training and the events...

00:14:19.500 --> 00:14:21.900
Plus the business trips
and the bridal project.

00:14:24.660 --> 00:14:26.340
You haven't had any time to actually rest.

00:14:28.410 --> 00:14:29.410
Yeah.

00:14:31.190 --> 00:14:33.420
But you've been just as busy, Natsume-san.

00:14:34.760 --> 00:14:35.760
I suppose.

00:14:37.480 --> 00:14:38.480
But still,

00:14:39.780 --> 00:14:41.250
everything with Hoshina-kun,

00:14:42.003 --> 00:14:43.123
and Yumihara-san...

00:14:44.820 --> 00:14:46.089
It's all been such a
great learning experience.

00:14:46.090 --> 00:14:47.440
So I think it was worth it.

00:14:49.060 --> 00:14:50.680
It was really valuable.

00:14:52.720 --> 00:14:53.720
And besides,

00:14:56.680 --> 00:14:57.910
after working that hard,

00:14:58.620 --> 00:15:00.580
this feels even better.
It makes it all worth it.

00:15:09.720 --> 00:15:13.430
You're a great person to travel with.

00:15:14.170 --> 00:15:14.810
Huh?

00:15:14.910 --> 00:15:16.670
Because your reactions are so over-the-top.

00:15:16.730 --> 00:15:18.170
Is that supposed to be a compliment?

00:15:20.610 --> 00:15:21.610
As for you,

00:15:22.170 --> 00:15:24.460
you should speak up more.

00:15:25.450 --> 00:15:27.070
Like when we were picking where to go.

00:15:34.370 --> 00:15:36.000
This place is great, though.

00:15:36.520 --> 00:15:39.650
There's a winery, a herb garden,

00:15:39.970 --> 00:15:41.540
and you can even go fruit picking.

00:15:41.930 --> 00:15:44.070
Oh, and I heard there's
a gemstone workshop.

00:15:47.670 --> 00:15:48.670
Hey.

00:15:49.460 --> 00:15:51.400
Don't you have anywhere you want to go?

00:15:52.440 --> 00:15:55.600
I want to go wherever you want to go.

00:16:04.610 --> 00:16:06.290
You really don't have a single preference?

00:16:06.580 --> 00:16:08.220
Like somewhere you want to see tomorrow,

00:16:08.380 --> 00:16:09.680
or something you want to eat?

00:16:11.710 --> 00:16:15.990
I want to go where you want to go,

00:16:16.480 --> 00:16:18.290
and eat what you want to eat.

00:16:22.080 --> 00:16:24.780
Fine! I know you're never going to change.

00:16:28.760 --> 00:16:31.030
Where should we go tomorrow, then?

00:16:55.570 --> 00:16:56.570
Oh!

00:16:56.600 --> 00:16:57.600
What?

00:16:58.550 --> 00:17:00.030
I haven't used the open-air bath yet.

00:17:03.560 --> 00:17:04.760
The open-air bath!

00:17:04.940 --> 00:17:06.010
The open-air bath!

00:17:07.690 --> 00:17:08.980
- Natsume-san.
- Yeah?

00:17:09.620 --> 00:17:11.760
Why do you need to bathe so many times?

00:17:14.030 --> 00:17:16.730
We're at a hot spring.
What else would I do?

00:17:21.790 --> 00:17:22.790
Oh.

00:17:23.090 --> 00:17:25.109
I'm going to the public
bath tomorrow morning too.

00:17:25.110 --> 00:17:26.999
Didn't you just go?

00:17:27.000 --> 00:17:28.649
No, they swap the men's and women's baths.

00:17:28.650 --> 00:17:29.930
So I have to try the other side.

00:17:30.160 --> 00:17:31.160
I see.

00:17:31.350 --> 00:17:34.000
I'll get up early while it's empty.
No complaining!

00:17:36.850 --> 00:17:37.850
What are you laughing at?

00:17:38.190 --> 00:17:39.190
Nothing.

00:17:39.300 --> 00:17:41.440
I just think you look so content.

00:17:41.930 --> 00:17:43.470
I'm so glad we could come here.

00:17:58.846 --> 00:18:00.646
I wonder when we'll
be able to do this again.

00:18:01.560 --> 00:18:02.620
Like...

00:18:09.040 --> 00:18:10.840
Maybe I could visit you,

00:18:16.020 --> 00:18:18.500
or we could go somewhere
when you come back to Japan.

00:18:24.640 --> 00:18:26.230
But you probably won't have much time.

00:18:27.843 --> 00:18:29.653
It might be a while.

00:18:38.860 --> 00:18:40.580
Going somewhere far away, eating good food,

00:18:40.700 --> 00:18:42.980
soaking in the baths,
and just zoning out...

00:18:44.650 --> 00:18:46.150
It makes you forget about reality.

00:18:48.570 --> 00:18:50.170
Isn't that a good thing once in a while?

00:18:50.530 --> 00:18:52.080
We're always so busy.

00:18:57.080 --> 00:18:58.080
Yeah...

00:19:07.700 --> 00:19:08.970
- Touma...
- Natsume-san...

00:19:11.900 --> 00:19:12.900
I love you.

00:19:14.500 --> 00:19:15.500
Oh.

00:19:16.080 --> 00:19:17.640
You beat me to it again.

00:19:33.740 --> 00:19:35.940
Man, that was a blast.

00:19:36.170 --> 00:19:37.500
I can tell.

00:19:38.650 --> 00:19:39.650
I'll drive.

00:19:41.230 --> 00:19:42.269
I thought I was driving?

00:19:42.270 --> 00:19:45.040
No, I'm less likely to
get carsick if I drive.

00:19:46.040 --> 00:19:47.040
Fair enough.

00:19:47.830 --> 00:19:48.910
I'll leave it to you, then.

00:19:49.070 --> 00:19:50.070
Okay.

00:19:53.020 --> 00:19:54.460
So, where to?

00:19:55.840 --> 00:19:56.940
Well, obviously...

00:19:57.430 --> 00:19:59.090
Fruit picking!

00:20:00.250 --> 00:20:05.280
Which one should I pick...?

00:20:05.880 --> 00:20:07.080
This is the one.

00:20:42.360 --> 00:20:43.360
Here.

00:20:44.260 --> 00:20:45.260
Thanks.

00:20:46.520 --> 00:20:48.190
- Let's eat!
- Let's eat!

00:20:51.310 --> 00:20:52.920
- So good!
- It's so sweet.

00:20:55.520 --> 00:20:56.720
I'm so glad we came.

00:21:05.300 --> 00:21:07.060
I should get some of these for my family.

00:21:09.150 --> 00:21:13.050
And then something for the shop...

00:21:17.310 --> 00:21:18.310
Let's go with this.

00:21:20.280 --> 00:21:22.400
Don't forget to buy
something for the Ginza store.

00:21:23.110 --> 00:21:24.210
I know.

00:21:25.620 --> 00:21:27.300
I have to get something for Nanjo-san too.

00:21:29.760 --> 00:21:31.480
Otherwise, he'll be a pain about it.

00:21:31.790 --> 00:21:33.669
A long weekend is pretty rare, huh?

00:21:33.670 --> 00:21:34.929
Where are you and Mamiya-kun going?

00:21:34.930 --> 00:21:36.680
Must be nice! Where to?

00:21:36.690 --> 00:21:39.210
The destination determines the quality
of the souvenir I expect!

00:21:39.330 --> 00:21:40.190
Somewhere abroad?

00:21:40.191 --> 00:21:42.190
Oh, Paris would be nice!

00:21:42.790 --> 00:21:43.790
How about this?

00:21:43.930 --> 00:21:44.930
No.

00:21:45.000 --> 00:21:46.720
Not if Natsume-san picks it.

00:21:47.110 --> 00:21:48.570
He'll be way too happy.

00:21:50.900 --> 00:21:53.740
Yeah, let's go with this one.

00:21:59.820 --> 00:22:01.140
Hey, what should we do for lunch?

00:22:02.470 --> 00:22:04.080
I'm not really that hungry, though.

00:22:04.440 --> 00:22:06.200
That's because you
ate so much at breakfast.

00:22:06.400 --> 00:22:08.610
You have to eat your
fill at a hotel buffet!

00:22:22.490 --> 00:22:23.490
By the way,

00:22:28.610 --> 00:22:29.610
actually...

00:22:31.720 --> 00:22:33.170
I bought this yesterday.

00:22:36.040 --> 00:22:37.040
Can I open it?

00:22:37.330 --> 00:22:38.330
Yeah.

00:22:42.980 --> 00:22:44.130
Mugs?

00:22:45.050 --> 00:22:47.180
One for you to take to Paris.

00:22:48.010 --> 00:22:49.240
And I'll keep the other one.

00:22:51.540 --> 00:22:52.890
So they're a matching set.

00:22:53.310 --> 00:22:54.410
Thank you.

00:22:55.110 --> 00:22:56.110
Yeah.

00:23:10.240 --> 00:23:11.440
Hey, Natsume-san.

00:23:13.430 --> 00:23:14.430
Yeah?

00:23:18.310 --> 00:23:19.510
Should we get rings?

00:23:25.840 --> 00:23:26.840
Huh?

00:23:28.850 --> 00:23:30.050
So that even when we're apart,

00:23:31.670 --> 00:23:32.930
we won't feel lonely.

00:23:41.220 --> 00:23:42.220
Yeah.

00:23:49.260 --> 00:23:51.890
I want to etch every
moment we spend together

00:23:53.210 --> 00:23:55.530
into my heart so they never slip away.

00:23:58.780 --> 00:24:00.980
We really are opposites in so many ways.

00:24:02.030 --> 00:24:03.960
We fight a lot too.

00:24:04.830 --> 00:24:05.830
Yeah.

00:24:09.090 --> 00:24:10.190
But I'm still so happy.

00:24:12.310 --> 00:24:13.310
Me too.

00:24:14.870 --> 00:24:16.070
Let's come back again.

00:24:16.910 --> 00:24:17.910
Definitely.

00:24:19.080 --> 00:24:20.080
I have to make sure

00:24:23.380 --> 00:24:25.020
while I'm still by your side,

00:24:25.610 --> 00:24:27.060
that I tell you everything

00:24:27.530 --> 00:24:28.730
I've been wanting to say.

00:24:29.920 --> 00:24:31.210
Even a moment of shyness,

00:24:31.770 --> 00:24:33.060
or time spent being stubborn,

00:24:33.690 --> 00:24:35.480
feels like such a waste.

00:24:39.210 --> 00:24:40.210
Touma.

00:24:47.250 --> 00:24:48.450
I love you so much.

00:25:03.490 --> 00:25:04.690
You're blushing.

00:25:06.610 --> 00:25:07.610
Shut up.

00:25:10.680 --> 00:25:11.680
I'm so happy.

00:25:11.970 --> 00:25:12.970
Say it again.

00:25:18.720 --> 00:25:19.720
I love you most.

00:25:23.260 --> 00:25:25.700
Have you been wanting
to say that all along?

00:25:28.350 --> 00:25:29.350
Maybe...

00:25:31.610 --> 00:25:33.100
Thank you.

00:25:34.040 --> 00:25:38.210
I love you most too, Natsume-san.

00:25:59.290 --> 00:26:01.380
Six months left

00:26:04.200 --> 00:26:05.520
until Touma leaves Japan.

00:26:30.840 --> 00:26:32.540
(Next Episode)
- Mamiya Natsume! - Huh?

00:26:32.790 --> 00:26:33.939
Come with me.

00:26:33.940 --> 00:26:36.950
Oh no! Touma is going to be
so mad when he sees this.

00:26:37.050 --> 00:26:38.399
Do you have any idea how worried I was?

00:26:38.400 --> 00:26:39.799
I said I was sorry, didn't I?

00:26:39.800 --> 00:26:41.040
You are seriously unbelievable.